<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-30-0386 </DOCNO><TEXT>There are four main sections to the book: background, current clinicalapplications, present and future departmental applications, and the personalcomputer. The reader is presented with a bonus in the section on currentclinical applications: erudite discussions of the physical backgroundof computed tomography, magnetic resonance, ultrasound, digital subtractionangiography, and nuclear medicine lead into the discussions of the mannerin which computers are used with each modality. Therefore, the readerobtains a perspective on the information each imaging modality has tooffer. The jargon is italicized in the body of the text and referencedto a glossary of terms in the back of the book. Some advice is includedin the sections on evaluating equipment for purchase, troubleshootingequipment, and using the personal computer.</TEXT></DOC>